Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.77,0:23:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Comment: 0,0:24:03.86,0:24:06.86,Note,,0,0,0,,{end}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.09,0:01:34.38,Top,,0,0,0,,We're twins. The younger one is Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:34.38,0:01:35.73,Top,,0,0,0,,The older one is Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.73,0:01:37.78,Top,,0,0,0,,Our parents plotted to transfer us
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.78,0:01:40.80,Top,,0,0,0,,from our beloved Redroofs School \Nto St. Clare's School.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.80,0:01:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We put up as much of a fight as we could, \Nbut it was no use.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.84,0:01:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So eventually, we resigned ourselves to it. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.62,0:01:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Our homeroom teacher, Miss Roberts, \Nis quite a stylish lady.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.04,0:01:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Matron is very scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.14,0:01:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems the headmistress is veiling \Nher kindness with strictness.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.70,0:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we're here, \Nwe'll have to give it our all. {lit: anyway, here, have to do it}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.90,0:02:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.68,0:02:20.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,So it begins.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.04,0:02:21.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's now or never.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.41,0:02:23.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,Don't forget last night's vow.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.14,0:02:24.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,How could I?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.08,0:02:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This school building is not bad either.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.98,0:02:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The breakfast is decent as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.65,0:02:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinner yesterday was up there too.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.36,0:02:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.56,0:02:38.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,Remember our vow last night?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.06,0:02:43.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Put the athletic and academic abilities of the O'Sullivan twins on display to blow everyone away.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.10,0:02:46.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Unleash a twin shock on St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.20,0:02:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a drill anymore. {/the real show starts now}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.97,0:02:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this time, it's for real.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.17,0:02:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.78,0:03:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Patricia and Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.35,0:03:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you solve this problem?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.27,0:03:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They never taught us this stuff back at Redroofs.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.16,0:03:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't this come later in the curriculum? {?? lit: Don't you learn it after you've gone further?}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.13,0:03:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's obvious we can't solve \Nsomething we've never been taught!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.93,0:03:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so awfully behind!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.50,0:03:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's Redroofs for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.89,0:03:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. However, you two \Ncannot rely on that excuse here. {lit: talking like that is a nono}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.34,0:03:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To grow up to be dignified ladies, \Nyou must learn to be more cooperative. {sunao = honest/obedient/modest - kinda a general word for something that means "a team player" as opposed to being snobs that they are now}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.86,0:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Cooperative?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.76,0:03:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is St. Clare's School, \Nnot Redroofs School.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.94,0:03:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you’re part of this school, make sure you put in the effort to keep up with our curriculum.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.59,0:03:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If there’s something you don’t know, just ask your classmates. I’ll be glad to help anytime too.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.43,0:03:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.66,0:03:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.20,0:03:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.96,0:04:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck! \NWhy did you say "Yes" so readily?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.49,0:04:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that? \NDidn't you say it yourself too?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.64,0:04:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I only parroted you without thinking. \NIt sure shook me to the core.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.84,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the standard of education here is pretty high.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.68,0:04:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.92,0:04:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But we need to rethink our strategy a bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.45,0:04:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Next period is gym class.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.92,0:04:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave it all to your sis.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.41,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll be playing lacrosse.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.91,0:04:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that just hockey in the air?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.36,0:04:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sport that I can't handle.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.50,0:04:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fair enough. \NThe honor of the O'Sullivan twins is on the line!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.50,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That looks doable.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.99,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to do it, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.94,0:04:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.54,0:04:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, pass to me! {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.88,0:04:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.08,0:04:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice goal, Pat! {actually "nice shoot"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.97,0:04:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really their first time playing?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.26,0:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! They're too good at it!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.85,0:05:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{ararara?}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.58,0:05:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda Towers is one really intimidating senior.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.35,0:05:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You should watch yourself around her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.32,0:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for it, Pat! {we see isabel now}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.81,0:05:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.65,0:05:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda Towers? She's a fifth former \Nand the captain of the lacrosse club.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.49,0:05:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Being intimidating is what she's famous for.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.51,0:05:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt any underclassman \Nhas ever escaped Belinda’s wrath.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.57,0:05:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she can bring it on for all I care! {lit: I'm fine with her being mad}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.97,0:05:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if she forbids you to go outside?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.67,0:05:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.60,0:05:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's that about?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.87,0:05:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren’t we free to go outside whenever we like after school?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.24,0:05:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you'd think. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.84,0:05:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality, it's impossible without permission from our seniors. {/the fifth and 6th graders}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.35,0:05:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.52,0:05:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we talk, Janet?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.62,0:05:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.39,0:05:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Kay Longden, the fifth former, wants you. \NYou’re to light the stove and make some toast for her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.16,0:05:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.06,0:05:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make her wait. {Reworded to be less ugly}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.08,0:06:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.84,0:06:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.52,0:06:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must you go help that arrogant person?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.71,0:06:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! \NI'd never agree to it if I were you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.38,0:06:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you have to light \Nsomeone else's stove?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.81,0:06:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what maids are for.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.91,0:06:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If she doesn't have one, \NKay should do it herself!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.35,0:06:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Something tells me you're next in line. {lit: it's your turn next}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.39,0:06:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch yourselves, our little twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.45,0:06:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.62,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two. You know seniors get their own study rooms for just one or two people, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.04,0:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There, they can drink tea and eat cakes, \Nand do whatever they want, freely.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.76,0:06:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All while the juniors are helping them out.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.33,0:06:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Juniors do what they're told to, \Nwithout objections.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.17,0:06:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the custom of our school. {/habit}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.72,0:06:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody here is complaining about it. {hara wo tatsu is more like "to rebel against/to get angry at"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.31,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we become seniors, \Nwe'll also be able to give orders to our juniors. {lit: will be in a position to use juniors}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.16,0:06:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents didn't send me to this school \Nto cater to lazy seniors!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.05,0:06:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we listen to their orders?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.80,0:07:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, you're a fool, you know that?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.12,0:07:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Being obstinate like this all the time \Nwill make you the public enemy of the school.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.91,0:07:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.29,0:07:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you get an order from Belinda.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.63,0:07:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When Belinda calls, she’ll keep piling errands on you without end.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.12,0:07:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst people are those who think they are somebodies, like you two,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.27,0:07:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when so often they are just nobodies. {from the book, the JP line says "You two seem to think you're special. That exactly the kind of people who are usually nothing special."}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.24,0:07:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If my parents heard of it, \Nthey'd probably tell me to stay away from you. {/advise me not to be friends with you}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.44,0:07:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?! {??? lit: said, didn't you}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.34,0:07:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Humph!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.38,0:07:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Come off your high horse, Sheila. \NThe twins aren’t that bad. {lit: you're saying too much}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.55,0:07:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we aren't!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.17,0:07:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm sure they'd be getting along with everyone just fine if someone knocked them down a peg. {lit: if only being argued into silence; being left speechless a bit, get along with everyone}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.16,0:07:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We should give them a chance. {lit: if only there's a chance/cue}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.56,0:07:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm mad now! {???? lit: no more}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.33,0:07:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to blow off some steam. {lit: isabel, let's do it - ???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.63,0:07:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.74,0:07:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One more!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.05,0:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you received a letter from them?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.32,0:08:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.92,0:08:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I did ask them to write, \Nbut it hasn’t even been a week yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.84,0:08:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... They must have enough \Nto worry about as it is. {lit: they're probably busy with different things}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.84,0:08:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.89,0:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, I'm sure those two are doing just fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.32,0:08:23.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,It’s the third day since we came to St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.17,0:08:32.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,So far, the customs of this school \Nhave given Pat and me nothing but shocks.  {lit: made us make round eyes = to stare in wonder; to be amazed}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.34,0:08:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, do you think the seniors are going to call on us too one day?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.74,0:08:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they do, we can just feign ignorance. {/pretend not to know what this is about/ignore them}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.19,0:08:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.30,0:08:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, has anyone seen the O'Sullivan twins?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.87,0:08:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda Towers wants one of you \Nto come to her room.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.45,0:08:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.27,0:08:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.81,0:09:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So it begins. {lit: there, it came}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.53,0:09:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.24,0:09:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.04,0:09:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But Belinda’s been out on the field all afternoon, \Nso she probably wants a shoe-cleaning.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.58,0:09:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, you'd better hurry it up. Bye.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.13,0:09:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you not going?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.78,0:09:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to stop with this silly protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.97,0:09:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One of you should go \Nand find out what Belinda needs.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.60,0:09:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For your own good, \Ndon't make Belinda wait. {lit: because I ask you}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.82,0:09:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make her come here, Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.41,0:09:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it’s all of us who’ll catch her wrath, not just Pat. {lit: hysteria will go father than pat - probably means "she'll make a scene and everyone will be caught up in it"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.34,0:09:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hurry up and go. \NIf you don't, she'll make a huge scene.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.15,0:09:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.30,0:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! It's beneath the O'Sullivan family \Nto clean other people's boots!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.59,0:09:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I just go and see what she needs... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.72,0:09:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! \NEither way, someone needs to go soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.39,0:09:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's actually for something \Ncompletely different.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.34,0:09:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NGet going already!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.43,0:10:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda has a very short temper. \NYou'll be in a world of trouble if you don't hurry.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.12,0:10:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Isabel, let's go together.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.00,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.04,0:10:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're only going there to ask what she needs.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.47,0:10:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.49,0:10:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to clean her boots or light her stove!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.78,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.99,0:10:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock, can’t you? \NBarging like that into someone else's room!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I should jolly well like to know \Nwhat took you so long!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.67,0:10:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, I only sent for one of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.67,0:10:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you just stand there speechless—\Nhaven’t you a tongue between you?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.36,0:10:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe these girls, Pamela!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.04,0:10:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.31,0:10:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as you’ve both come, \Nyou can both do a spot of work for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.45,0:10:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Light up that stove for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.48,0:10:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Put the kettle on to boil \Nand clean our boots.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.65,0:10:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going out to collect our prep, \Nand we need it done by the time we get back.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.47,0:10:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go, Pamela.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.53,0:11:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hold on a minute!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.23,0:11:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't come to St. Clare's \Nto babysit seniors!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.38,0:11:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.97,0:11:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We refuse to clean your boots \Nor boil water for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.39,0:11:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t believe my ears! \NWhere’d they dig up girls this full of themselves?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.67,0:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's a kicker, young ladies. {lit: understand, ladies}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.27,0:11:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say goodbye \Nto going outside any time soon!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.04,0:11:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You got that?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.81,0:11:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No! We won't accept it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.41,0:11:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Seniors or not, \Nyou're in no position to forbid us that! {lit: no matter how fifth grader, you don't have that right, I think}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.33,0:11:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hearing what I'm hearing, Pamela?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.62,0:11:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard an underclassman talk like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.77,0:11:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not once in the history of St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.16,0:11:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be a huge problem!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.64,0:11:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A huge problem?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.25,0:11:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start by going to Winifred James, \Nthe head-girl, and ask her to arbitrate for us! {lit: anyway, student council president 6th grader Winifred James - ask her which of us is right}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.25,0:11:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see how you sing then!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.80,0:12:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, wouldn't it be better to just \Ndo as they say and not escalate this any further?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.59,0:12:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious! \NI'm gonna fight my way through!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.66,0:12:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.00,0:12:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We're this year's newcomers.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.07,0:12:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.68,0:12:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.11,0:12:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Winifred.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.18,0:12:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you also had the same hairstyle, \Nit'd be impossible to tell you two apart.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.08,0:12:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get this study room all to yourself?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.48,0:12:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.68,0:12:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{Wow}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.79,0:12:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, did you want something?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.64,0:12:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.46,0:12:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda, the fifth former, \Nsays we have to clean her boots,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.20,0:12:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,light her stove, and boil her kettle—\Nand if we refuse, we’re banned from going outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.07,0:12:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be acceptable?! {/allowed - meaning "there's no way it's true, right?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.62,0:12:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really come to ask me about that?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.71,0:12:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in this school, the juniors \Nare to wait on the seniors within reason. {lit: Well, if the upperclassman's order is reasonable, the underclassmen must follow it.}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.58,0:12:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that another custom of St. Clare's?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.95,0:13:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you know that, do as you're told \Nand help them with their errands.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.55,0:13:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they say? \NWhen in Rome, do as the Romans do.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.32,0:13:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the way St. Clare's does it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.42,0:13:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t want to follow silly customs of that sort!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.09,0:13:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you should wait a little while \Nbefore calling our customs silly.

Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.03,0:13:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can’t you girls clean boots?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.36,0:13:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you know how to light a stove? \NHave you never put a kettle on to boil?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.70,0:13:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We never had to back at Redroofs.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.14,0:13:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we were at home, I don’t think \Nwe’d know how to clean muddy boots!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.64,0:13:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that is just sad! {/I'm stunned; was "Good heavens!" in book}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.81,0:13:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To think you don’t know \Nhow to clean boots at your age! {again, in book she says "at almost 15"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.42,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All the more reason \Nwhy you should learn at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.09,0:13:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to Belinda’s study \Nand try to do what she tells you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.83,0:13:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.63,0:13:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if it means \Nnot going to town once this whole term,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.88,0:13:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,who'd want to clean Belinda's beastly dirty boots?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.99,0:14:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, but I did want \Nto get a new set of hairgrips... {hairpin}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.41,0:14:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course I wanna go to the town too!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.92,0:14:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, haven't we resisted enough? \NIf we just suck it up now and help Belinda...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.71,0:14:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then feel free to do it on your own!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.75,0:14:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, I'm definitely not going to do anything for them!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.95,0:14:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.22,0:14:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Pat, you stick in the mud... {Obstinate person}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.13,0:14:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.97,0:14:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something troubling you?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.54,0:14:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.91,0:14:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. {That 'if so' seemed unnecessary}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.47,0:14:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Matron...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.41,0:14:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel, not Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.76,0:14:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my bad, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.71,0:14:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are so awfully alike!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.62,0:14:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Isabel, see you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.59,0:14:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's a great plan! {/idea}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.09,0:14:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.99,0:14:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They left already?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.43,0:15:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how do I clean these?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.73,0:15:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a bit of help?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.92,0:15:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.31,0:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,First, scrap them and get all the clay off.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.26,0:15:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.17,0:15:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this, see?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.20,0:15:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.33,0:15:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Next you rinse them with water.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.62,0:15:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now to light the stove \Nand put the kettle on to boil.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll start the fire, \Nmeanwhile you fill the kettle.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.76,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.59,0:15:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, I'm really grateful—\Nyou're a lifesaver!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.02,0:15:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.63,0:15:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just glad I could help. {/make you happy}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.49,0:15:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.97,0:15:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fun today.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.67,0:15:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.64,0:15:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you got lost. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.21,0:15:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.98,0:15:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.95,0:15:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you decided to be sensible, I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.09,0:15:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But where’s your twin?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.16,0:15:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't help, did she?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.32,0:16:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tell her that there’ll be no going \Ndown to town for her!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.66,0:16:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I won’t have new girls \Nbehaving as if they own the place! {lit: despite being newcomer, I won't allow such cocky behavior}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.30,0:16:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Word-for-word! {/make sure to tell her}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.10,0:16:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.10,0:16:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the kettle boiling yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.28,0:16:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness, it's still cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.44,0:16:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve only put it on just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.66,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn’t occur to you to put the kettle on first, \Nbefore you did the boots?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.95,0:16:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How is something like that not obvious to you? {lit: there's such thing as order in things - not in book}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.32,0:16:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a lot more common sense\Nwhen I was your age. {/in 1st grade}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.48,0:16:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can clear out now. And see that you come running next time I send a message!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.59,0:16:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.93,0:16:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, one more thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.68,0:16:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you tell that obstinate \Ntwin of yours what I said.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.23,0:16:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If she keeps disobeying us, \NI’ll report her to the headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.44,0:16:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She can report me all she wants! \NI know I did nothing wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.58,0:16:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, \Nwhy did you obey that brute Belinda?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.28,0:16:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it’d just be easier \Nto set everything right that way. {lit: if I go "aah, screw it, I'll do it" everything will go well [for us]}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.20,0:16:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.72,0:17:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean set everything right? {/go well}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.69,0:17:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't there with you, \Nso I still can't leave the campus.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.41,0:17:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.88,0:17:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes you think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.40,0:17:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just copy my hairstyle and you can pass for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.37,0:17:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, that's a good idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.48,0:17:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how about it?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.55,0:17:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It suits you well, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.25,0:17:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.35,0:17:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll show that Belinda. {/take revenge - Reworded to be less clunky}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.36,0:17:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.13,0:17:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.42,0:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely love going out. {says it in the past tense for some reason - either means "at my old school" or "fell in love with it [while being here]"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.38,0:17:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think its important to unwind every once in a while, Isabel?  {/take a breather}{dunno how to frame this as a question}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.74,0:17:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.40,0:18:02.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wonder what Pat \Nis doing in town right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.83,0:18:05.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,We'll switch back tomorrow \Nand I'll go to town.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.82,0:18:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.02,0:18:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia O'Sullivan?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.72,0:18:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you Patricia O'Sullivan?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.02,0:18:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's me.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.79,0:18:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda sent for you, come at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.01,0:18:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda did?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.63,0:18:24.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I... I hope she doesn't see through it. {/expose me}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.67,0:18:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia O'Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.96,0:18:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.57,0:18:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re a silly, obstinate kid, but I’m not holding that against you where lacrosse is concerned. {from book, lit: although you don't listen to what seniors say, ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.36,0:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.83,0:18:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was watching the last few practices, \Nand I can't deny that you're good at lacrosse.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.92,0:18:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m putting you down \Nfor the match on Saturday.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.31,0:18:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.39,0:18:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As the captain of the team, \NI have to leave my personal feelings out.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.67,0:18:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.39,0:19:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, hear this! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.98,0:19:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.15,0:19:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, come on now, what's all the rush?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.28,0:19:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! Belinda's signed you up \Nfor the next lacrosse match!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.46,0:19:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This upcoming Saturday!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.96,0:19:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What? She'd let me play in the match already?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.83,0:19:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.48,0:19:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...? But isn't she Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.42,0:19:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, you did it! {/it's a success}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.39,0:19:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.83,0:19:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If she was really as mean as we thought her to be,  \Nshe’d have left me out for months.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.38,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda must actually be very forgiving. {lit: heard is vast}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.88,0:19:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Pat, what is...{??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.57,0:20:07.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,222)}Pat, I know exactly what you're thinking!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.98,0:20:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Belinda's study now!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.39,0:20:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Isabel? \NI didn't send for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.53,0:20:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat. It's about Saturday's game.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.90,0:20:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat? If you're just here to pull my leg...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.53,0:20:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's true!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.15,0:20:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you talked to earlier was Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.37,0:20:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was down in town, \Npretending to be Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.87,0:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I thought it was \Na rather smart trick to pay you out.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.91,0:20:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I realize it was a sly \Nand cowardly thing to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.38,0:20:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel embarrassed for resorting to it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.30,0:20:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve come to say thank you \Nfor putting me in the match,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.76,0:21:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but of course, now that I've done this, \NI don’t expect to actually play.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.13,0:21:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.93,0:21:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll take my share of the work with Isabel now, \Nno matter what kind of task it is. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.28,0:21:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I was foolish, sly, and mean before. \NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.25,0:21:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something to say too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.42,0:21:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve done something rather mean, \Nbut you’ve been big enough to make it right. {from book, lit: it takes a lot of courage to admit you've done something wrong}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.00,0:21:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our opponent in Saturday's match is strong. \NDo your best.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.06,0:21:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.13,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, you're full of yourself and stubborn,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.10,0:21:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so I want you to throw all \Nof that fighting spirit into lacrosse.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.94,0:21:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lacrosse is the kind of sport \Nthat requires that fighting spirit you have.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.58,0:21:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.52,0:22:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, Pat! \NNice shot! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:16.97,0:22:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.02,0:23:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate conjugating French verbs,\Nthey’re such a pain in the neck!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.77,0:23:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must we learn French at all?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.99,0:23:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,True! And our French teacher is so strict too!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.66,0:23:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle, huh? {we hear Mademoiselle but in the book it's mam'zelle, will stick with that}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.36,0:23:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ah, abominable!" {??? assuming she's parroting their teacher or soemthing}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.33,0:23:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! {ye seems i guessed right}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.17,0:23:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel, let's call that teacher "Mam’zelle Abominable" from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.25,0:23:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.40,0:23:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins of St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.87,0:24:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mam’zelle Abominable."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.29,0:24:04.79,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 3\NMam’zelle Abominable {嘆きのマドモアゼル}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.17,0:24:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
